Build (on Linux):

0. Install Flutter SDK (and Dart).
1. Setup Android Toolchain (with Android Studio or Manually).
2. Verify the configuration (run `flutter doctor`), A successful configuration example:

> $ flutter doctor
Doctor summary (to see all details, run flutter doctor -v):
[✓] Flutter (Channel stable, 3.24.4, on Fedora Linux 40 (Workstation Edition)
    6.11.5-200.fc40.x86_64, locale en_US.UTF-8)
[✓] Android toolchain - develop for Android devices (Android SDK version 35.0.0)
[✓] Android Studio (version 2024.2)
[✓] VS Code (version 1.94.1)
[✓] Connected device (2 available)
[✓] Network resources

3. Install project dependencies (run `flutter pub get`).
4. Build APK for arm64 (run `flutter build apk --target-platform android-arm64`).
5. Get the APK from `./build/app/outputs/flutter-apk`.

